insta_description:
For the past several years, #MCP along with collaborators from @ibo_at_boisestate @cbbep deployed #satellitetransmitters on #LongbilledCurlews a species of conservation concern, to unravel the mysteries of its annual and life #cycles. Through our #tracking efforts, we have learned a lot about the #connections between breeding and wintering grounds of Long-billed Curlews in the intermountain west, the valleys of #California, and northern #Mexico. And we‚Äôve learned about their migrations from the central and northern prairies of the U.S. and Canada to the #Texas #GulfCoast Most recently, we discovered the movements of curlews from disappearing wintering populations in the Southeastern US, tracking a male from its wintering grounds in #Georgia to the prairies of #Saskatchewan #Canada (Read more from our expedition blogs here http://www.migratoryconnectivityproject.org/expedition-blog/southeast-curlews-december-2015/). Despite all of our efforts, we still have not tracked a curlew to #coastal California, even though we know that thousands of individuals from this species winter there. Along with partners Jay Carlisle and Intermountain Bird Observatory & Curlew Crew, Nils Warnock and Audubon Canyon Ranch, David Newstead and Coastal Bend Bays and Estuaries, we headed out to the beaches and mudflats of Bolinas/Point Reyes, California about an hour north of #SanFrancisco to capture curlews on their wintering grounds in hopes of finding out where this wintering population breeds. We successfully captured and deployed transmitters on 2 curlews, 1 male and 1 female. Stay tuned as we find out where these coastal California curlews breed! Photo credits: Neil Clipperton, Scott Jennings, David Newstead

We are only allowed to leave our house for ‚Äònecessary activities‚Äô such as getting groceries, seeing a doctor, getting gas, or caring for family members/pets that need help in another household. Outdoor activities such as walking your dog, running, or hiking are allowed as long as you keep at least 6 feet away from others. ‚Å£
‚Å£
In order to slow down the spread of the virus and flatten the curve, it is important that we all try our best to follow these social distancing steps. These steps can break potential chains of transmission by preventing contacts between the infected and healthy ones. Everyone needs to do their part for this to work effectively; collectively we can slow this virus from continued further spread, which is important because that can help our health services and medical workers from becoming overburdened.‚Å£
‚Å£
Even if you are currently living in a place that doesn‚Äôt have many confirmed cases yet and think that you do not have to do anything different, you should still start practicing social distancing and keeping up with your personal hygiene now if you haven‚Äôt already. To tackle this disease, you have to be one step ahead and take extra precautions before the curve becomes exponential. Given the long incubation period of this disease, the number of cases in the next 2 weeks depend on what you do today. You can still make a change starting now. #flattenthecurve‚Å£
‚Å£
Social distancing things you can do:‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Ä£ Work from home if you can‚Å£
‚Ä£ Avoid gatherings‚Å£
‚Ä£ Cancel unnecessary travel‚Å£
‚Ä£ Avoid public places (lines, restaurants, gyms, bars, malls‚Ä¶etc)‚Å£
‚Ä£ Try out grocery delivery services if available‚Å£
‚Å£
If you have to go out to the public:‚Å£
‚Å£
‚Ä£ Stay at least 6 feet away from others‚Å£
‚Ä£ Don‚Äôt touch your face, eyes, nose, or mouth‚Å£
‚Ä£ Avoid high touch items such as doorknobs, handrails, & elevator buttons‚Å£
‚Ä£ Wear glasses to minimize the risk of unwanted droplets flying in‚Å£
‚Ä£ Wash your hands frequently with soap for 20 seconds (continued in comments)

What a week! How are you handling all this change? ‚Å£ü§Ø
‚Å£
I‚Äôll admit it‚Äôs been intense! And last night with new restrictions that stated our family should stick in home for 3 months it was a lot to process. ‚Å£
‚Å£
But as others have said, this can be a good time to flip your perspective. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Here are my beginning thoughts on how I plan to get through this: ‚Å£
‚Å£
- I‚Äôve kept saying I need to meditate more. Well - this is a perfect time to start!‚Å£ üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è ‚Å£
- Exercise, every day. Find a way, whether it‚Äôs a walk or bike around the block, yoga at home, a run, ordering some weights. Keep moving. It‚Äôs good for your mind, it‚Äôs good for your body. It‚Äôs just plain good for you. ‚Å£üí™
‚Å£
- What are the projects you‚Äôve wanted to get done? I want to patch the trim and have more time to write. That‚Äôs hard, with little ones around, but we‚Äôre not running around as much so the time should follow. I also want to help my daughter start to learn to read. I‚Äôm not going to make a flow chart of her schooling - she‚Äôs 3 1/2 - but I think it would be fun to start setting some goals for her too. üßπ‚Å£
‚Å£
- Appreciate the little things. I‚Äôve really loved seeing my family snuggling more, playing in the yard, etc. Stop to smell the flowers on your walk, take a bubble bath or lay out and look at the sky. Look for little mindful moments you can find something you appreciate and soak it in. ‚Å£üõÄ
‚Å£
- Experiment. It seems like we‚Äôre going to have some strange food mixes for a bit. What can you make? What new things can you try? It‚Äôs not great to be forced to change, but change can be good too.‚Å£ ‚Å£
What are your ideas? I‚Äôd love to hear more!‚Å£

HIIT body weight + resistance band AT HOME üè° Okay so we are all basically social distancing and staying at home, I hope! Staying at home can be nice for about 2-3 days and then after that trust me if you‚Äôre not doing things to keep yourself active and keep your mind at ease, you will develop anxiety and just start to feel low. Try out this home workout, play your favourite playlist out loud and just follow through. If you‚Äôre not someone who likes to workout try to do things like de-clutter, organize that pantry, bake a cake, or spend time with your loved ones at home of course. If you are stuck at home with abusive or toxic people, reach out to someone for help, FaceTime your friends, do your best to just not let your mind go there. It is so tough and if you know someone who might be in that situation, try to reach out to them. ALSO if you see an elderly person trying to buy groceries and they are standing at the back of the line to checkout, freakin let them go in front of you!!! insta_description:
üß±üí™üèøMore Stability Ball Plank Variations! This time with @eggweights - Single Leg Plank Hamstring Curls - This is a very challenging movement, that requires a strong posterior chain (backside of the body). The glutes must remain engaged to keep the hips elevated. At the same time the hamstring complex goes through an intense series of concentric/eccentric (shortening/lengthening contractions) all while staying isometrically engaged. In other words this movement requires stabalization to get into the correct starting position, and then requires immense stabalization as the single leg curls the stability ball inwards to a triple flexed position, and then extends the same leg out. 
I could quite literally feel the micro tears in my hamstrings as I went through this pattern, which is a great thing in my opinion. So make sure your body (hamstrings in particular) are adequately warmed up so you can get the most out of this movement. I feel as though this curl variation requires similar engagement by the glutes and hamstrings as hip/back extensions on a standard glute/ham machine. Both variations require the torso to remain steady in a plank, while the hamstring and glutes work vigorously as a pair to leverage body weight, and create/resist movement.

Athletes give this movement a try on recovery days, or as an auxiliary lift to compliment heavy strength or explosive power days. They are another exercise that can point out weak links along your kinetic chain, and help to correct them. They help to strengthen the hamstrings in a way that is synonymous with sprinting (one leg flexed, the other extended). The mind/ body also have to think, move, and react constantly to maintain the lower case "h" position. This in turn helps to open neural pathways and leaves the body feeling more balanced. Exercises to Compliment S/L Hamstring Curls:

1) Deadlifts 2) Squats 3) Lunges 4) Sprints 5) Olympic Lifts 6 ) Box Step Ups/ Box Jumps

There are several differences between these two, avocados from Mexico traditionally are on the tree for a shorter time due to being closer to the equator and are available year around. Meanwhile California avocados are on the tree longer due to the colder weather creating a thicker skin and are able to develop a richer taste with more healthy oils. insta_description:
I can‚Äôt thank God enough for giving me sisters and giving me this moment of joy & happiness. With everything going on we decided to go to the beach and enjoy some fresh air, Saturday after Ali got home. When we showed up the clouds were dark and gloomy and the air around us was heavy. As we sat there talking about life, lots of baby talk mainly, and watching ali throw Karma‚Äôs toy.. all my anxiety and fears slowly washed away. I felt blissful for a moment, thankful that I got to sit there with my sisters and just enjoy their presence. We weren‚Äôt talking about how Ali‚Äôs senior year at Alabama is basically over and the slim chances of her getting to walk across that graduation stage, the first one in our family btw! Or my sister‚Äôs baby shower that we canceled to keep our loved ones safe and how she‚Äôs becoming a first time mom in an environment as chaotic as this... We laughed at how Karma chases the waves, we talked about baby Z coming into this world and what she‚Äôs going to be like, we forgot about all the heaviness. Minutes later, the clouds started to break and the sun was shining through! As we walked back the air got warmer and the beach felt more alive! The energy was completely different. Ali‚Äôs home visit was cut short due to fear of being stuck in California and all I can wish is that this whole pandemic is cut short, but really all I can do is play my part to keep others safe & healthy and I will highly advise others to do the same. The world works in mysterious ways and I have to believe that everything happens for a reason. Whether this moment in time teaches you to be mindful of others, allows you to reconnect with yourself and loved ones, or shows you the importance of personal health & safety, there is a reason for everything. There is beauty in every day, we just have to look for it! Xx, Kaari ü§ç ‚Ä¢

insta_description:
cliffside ‚Äî looking out into this seascape of rocks and cliffs today, i wonder how this place will change in the next few years, or even few hundred years.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
the cliffs will slowly erode, the sand will slowly retreat, and the rocks will break off into smaller ones.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
and then one day, a cliffside might collapse after the foundation below had given away.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
change is inevitable with time, the question is how will you deal with it?
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
the pandemic today has brought change on a global scale, and it's scary because it happened so fast and we're uncertain about the future and what may happen next.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
while i wish for this to be over with already so we can go back to our normal lives, i've been focusing how to make the best of the current situation.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
staying at home over the last few days, i've been able to really sit down and grind out some long overdue tasks such as redesigning my website and finishing my taxes that i had been putting off doing for weeks now.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
at the end of the day, i feel like this is a good time to make use of the time to do some self reflection, some work, and maybe play some fortnite.

This was my first time ever trying an 'Impossible' Burger. Well, now I know the impossible is possible. The texture was the same as a soft, juicy beef burger cooked on the BBQ. It was topped with gruyere, red wine-caramelized onions, arugula, fig mustard and a brioche bun served with rosemary potato wedges.

The second dish we ate was the Spicy Kale Caesar, the crispy shallots added so much more flavour and texture than I expected.

The restaurant itself, located right on Abbot Kinney, is one of the coolest, interior decorated restaurant I've ever been to. It has a beach/bohemian type look and feel. The space is so well utilized to fit all the hungry customers and the service was great.

I can tell you personally, I just about have a complete set and use one or more herb blends in everything I cook.¬†They are so good!
.
Last night I cooked a grass-fed Ribeye steak, sweet potato hash & made a fresh salad w/greens from our garden and an avocado. .
STEAKS
.
Season with Rosemary Crush, Black peppercorns, and Whole Latka Love. Give each side a nice pan sear in some butter or oil for a few minutes and finish cooking the steak in the oven around 400. Don‚Äôt forget to let them rest for a few minutes room temp before cutting and serving. 
SWEET POTATO HASH
.
Boil your sweet potatoes (or normal spuds) for a couple minutes until newly tender, strain and set aside. This is a good time to season with Secret Garden Blend or any of our other Shemesh blends that sound delish. Using the steak pan and all the bits left in after you seared the steaks, add in a bit of Shemesh honey (if you‚Äôve been rationing), butter and then fry up those potatoes.¬†I added some chopped green onions too. Extra seasoning when they hit the plate.
.
You folks know what to do with avocadoes and salads. ENJOY!!! And if you‚Äôve never used our blends, please order a couple online.¬†Link in the bio üëÜüëÜ. Our store is open as long as the post office is!

As California quickly settles into a new reality with restrictions on going outside and non-essential errands we‚Äôve decided to offer our health care services at a heavily discounted price for new members. From today we‚Äôre reducing the price to $0 per month for the first 3 months of care for all new members. üôå

Steady is the first full-service digital diabetes clinic in the US. We combine the power of continuous glucose monitors and the convenience of telemedicine to deliver a new type of care to patients. We know that diabetes is a chronic disease that is always present in life, it doesn‚Äôt follow a quarterly schedule or wait for your next visit. So, why should your doctor? Steady provides all of our care digitally using text messaging and video.
Our licensed medical team specializes in diabetes care and has years of experience both helping people manage it and living with the disease themselves. It also doesn‚Äôt matter if you are Type 1 or 2, or what kind of medication you are on. If you need help managing your blood sugar, we‚Äôre here to help.

Steady usually charges a monthly subscription fee of $60 per month to get access to our digital platform where you can easily connect and share data with our doctors and nurses. From today we‚Äôre reducing the price to $0 per month for the first 3 months of care for all new members.

All other services Steady provides, like visits with our Endocrinologists, are covered by insurance. We‚Äôre currently in network with several plans across California like Cigna, Aetna, HealthNet, Blue Shield and Anthem.

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: sky, night and outdoor
insta_description:
12/31/19. Los Angeles. I went searching for fireworks and skylines on the last day of the year. I wandered around for hours, and I ended up finding much more than skylines. In the city of perpetual traffic, I found peace. 
The months leading up to that day, I felt gradually more and more lost. What seemed like a good year started to unravel in retrospect. The loose ends that I left untied for so long began to tangle together. Instead of embracing the uncertainty as possibility, I wondered why I didn't have it all together.

There's something about the physical act of searching that helps us find ourselves. I got to LA way later than I had planned. I had effectively an hour and a half to capture the skyline from three different points: Hermosa Park. Dept. of Water, and Chinatown. As a photog, you learn quickly that lighting can change from good to bad in 5 minutes. It can make or break a shot.

Running around, frantically shooting gave me a clarity I hadn't felt in years. I didn't have time to think about my shots, let alone ruminate about my failures. The sun was setting fast. I stopped even reviewing my shots. Near the end of it, I got this photo. It's one of my favorites. And then I went from frantic to triumphant, as I started taking several of my best photos within minutes of each other. 
And then I knew: I'd never be lost as long as I had this.
_____

insta_description:
What a whirlwind but fun weekend Emma and I had. In 55 hours we were able to explore La Jolla and kayak in La Jolla Cove (definitely flipped my kayak) while celebrating St. Patrick‚Äôs Day with a fancy hat and beard (many kayakers had a good laugh and yelled Happy St. Patrick‚Äôs Day to us!) have a birthday party with some of the coolest people, meet new friends, drive around Coronado Island and see Naval Air Station North Island and walk around the Silver Strand and the Naval Amphibious Base Coronado (where the Navy Seals train for BUDS) trek around Point Loma and Cabrillo National Monument (tide pools and lighthouse included), play kickball at Kate O Sessions Memorial Park, walk and scooter around Balboa Park, geocaching along the way, look at all the amazing roses and succulents at Inez Grant Parker Memorial Rose Garden, eat California burritos, and watch planes land at the San Diego International Airport while sipping fancy drinks in Little Italy.  Honestly, one of the best birthday weekends I‚Äôve had in a long time filled with friends and laughter! Thanks for visiting, @emmaschultz25 and thanks to everyone who made this a very special weekend! Til next time!

accessibility_caption: Image may contain: possible text that says 'SUPPORT YOUR LOCAL SMALL BUSINESSES'
insta_description:
Earlier today the White House announced it may give Americans up to $1k to combat the economic devastation from the coronavirus outbreak.¬†However, it won't be enough for the economy and sm businesses to survive.¬†The Governor of FL also announced 2day all bars & clubs must shutdown for the nxt 30 days.¬†The devastation to the hotel & hospitality restaurant industry will be catastrophic if something more isn't done immediately. Let's review the data.¬†As recent as the 2017 census there are 28.7M sm bus in the US w/ 88% of those have fewer than 20 employees. This equals 25.2M businesses employing over 56.8M people; or 48% of all US employees.¬†According to a study from JPMorgan Chase sm business account for 45% of the US economies GDP.
All of the major banks, creditors & lending institutions (all of whom were bailed out in 2008 & reported record earnings in 2019) should defer all loan, mortgage, & credit card payments for 90 days while the entire country works collectively together in a quarantined environment to flatline this virus. This will allow landlords to delay rent payments without having to foot the bill & in most cases provide more than a $1k in relief to Americans who need the help.
Please note I said "defer" payments NOT "forgive." Lenders & creditors can add the deferred payments onto the backside of the loan or note. This will give small businesses & their employees the "cash flow" needed to weather the storm. It is imperative we learn from history. In 2008 we experienced the adverse impact of missed commercial loan, mortgage & credit card payments. The coronavirus pandemic is far more catastrophic. A Nationwide quarantine will result with people missing work & earning no wages to pay bills. No manufacturing companies producing goods, no transportation companies moving those products, no stores open to sell those goods & products. Additionally, expect a halt in construction & immediate shutdown of travel, entertainment & hospitality. Without an aggressive plan to support sm bus & their employees the consequences will be incalculable. More than a decade later we are facing a plethora of additional shortcomings far more devastating to the economy than 2008

insta_description:
To My Dear Clients and Greater Community, ‚Å£
‚Å£
I hope this note finds you well. Many are curious about the state of the real estate market and our business practices during this worldwide pandemic, so we wanted to take a moment to address what it means for our little corner of the world.‚Å£
‚Å£
Interest rates are at an all time low, as many of you know, and we are still seeing multiple offers on properties. Many of our agents held open houses this weekend, in which extra care was taken to keep things sanitized and safe. Many buyers came through and are ready to buy. This tells us that people need a place to call home, even in times of crisis. ‚Å£
‚Å£
That said, we want to do all that we can to keep the community safe and respect limits for social contact. In this respect, Compass has compassionately developed a Real Estate Best Practices Protocol to keep the community safe during this time of necessary social distancing.‚Å£
‚Å£
If you are looking to buy or sell a home, please contact us, and we can find a way safely work together to meet your needs. Moving forward, Compass Concierge and Bridge Loan Advance will be temporarily paused while we wait out the spread of the Coronavirus. We are happy to chat more about your options if you have a need for these programs. ‚Å£
‚Å£
While we are still operating our business, shared Compass offices are closed for now. We are still here to support you and answer any questions you may have via phone or email (or even DM here!).‚Å£
‚Å£
We are sending good thoughts out to all of you and to the greater world we live in. Stay safe and be well, dear community. And talk soon!‚Å£
‚Å£
Sincerely,‚Å£
Tim Little & Associates team‚Å£
‚Å£

insta_description:
ùó™ùêûùêöùê≠ùê°ùêûùê´ ùêúùê°ùêöùêßùê†ùêûùê¨ üåß üå¶‚òÄÔ∏è‚Å£
-‚Å£
Our weather changes all the time. Some times we have bright sunny days where we can go out and plan and everything seems great. Other times the weather isn‚Äôt so great and we are dealing with lots of snow or rain and need to stay inside. ‚Å£
-‚Å£
I remember doing my grad school in Utah and the weather there is WAY different than California. In CA we often have sunny day in the Central Valley (where I live) with some overcast days or even some rainy days here and there. In Utah it was a whole lot different. We had rain, hail, snow, overcast, and sunny days (some times all in the same day). The weather conditions in Utah were way different than CA, but I have never thought the subpar weather conditions I have faced would last forever. ‚Å£
-‚Å£
I want to give you some hope and remind you that this too shall pass. Nothing will last forever, good or bad. Yes the conditions we are facing now suck (let‚Äôs just be honest), but we will have sunny days ahead. Let‚Äôs look forward to and keep our eyes on the sunny days ahead. ‚Å£
-‚Å£
If they helped to brighten your day just a bit, please share it with someone who could use a little more sun in their life. ‚Å£

Alright babes, the past couple days you guys all have seen me posting a lot on working out and how its changing my life. As a mom of two & a wife its easy to put yourself last. i finally stepped up to a challenge! I'm making 30 minutes out of my day to do what makes me feel AMAZING!!! I'm on day 3 of this challenge and i can't wait to see where it takes me. I'm just going to be real with you guys. This is also another BIG reason why i am choosing me and my health, about a month ago i went and did my yearly eye exam. I was tested for glaucoma, my pressure came back high, so i went back a week later and did the test again, its still was high, so now I'm waiting for my next appointment to do more testing. My friends and family sent me some information on glaucoma.I read a lot on what i should and shouldn't be eating. Our nutrition is so important. 
I‚Äôm taking this big leap in my life to make a change for me. Hearing that i could have Glaucoma is extremely hard. but I'm going to fight for myself and do what i need to do for ME.
Have you ever challenged yourself?

Just wanted to thank the guys that helped me with dive information about California along the way that made this possible: @bigjimspearo @matttitch @reynaudalex @midhandle @zpearo @blake__mcfarland @orville_villanueva.  Funny Story: Got in the water and proceeded to drop half of the weight off my weight belt and stringer in 50ft of water so I had to start recovering that while being super buoyant. Found some of the weight, but not all, throughout a couple dives. On my final dive on the spot I found the last two lead weights and saw this lingcod as I turned to swim to the surface (I guess the noise attracted him). So I shot him with 5 pounds of lead in one hand at 50ft with not too much breath left and luckily stoned him free swimming away from me! That was my final dive because as I put the fish in my kayak the winds picked up and the swell doubled to white caps so I had to zoom in to shore. #makospearguns #spearfishing #speargun #lingcod #california #monterrey #dinner #kayakfishing #makowetsuits
